2.1.2 A maximum of one chair per square metre may be located in an 
alfresco dining area subject to any restrictions imposed by other laws 
including but not limited to the Building Code of Australia;

2.1.3 A 2m wide minimum footpath is to be provided and maintained clear 
of all obstructions including light poles, street furniture chairs, tables, 
pot plants and balustrading at all times;

2.1.6 All alfresco dining areas shall be clearly demarcated on site and all 
chairs, tables and fittings shall remain within the demarcated area at 
all times;

2.2.2 All furniture shall be of a high quality and shall be in keeping with the 
style and materials of furniture provided within the eating 
establishment;

2.3.1 To provide shade and shelter high quality awnings or market 
umbrellas are encouraged. The canopy of the umbrella must be 
higher than 2.3m from the pavement;

2.3.3 Screens more than 1m in height, including glass or perplex panels or 
clear plastic rolled down from umbrellas and awnings are not 
permitted;

4.6 The serving of alcohol shall not commence unless the relevant approval has 
been obtained from the Liquor Licensing Division of the Office of Racing and 
Gaming;

4.8 Tables and chairs placed in a public place that enables unlimited public use 
shall not be considered as part of the premises in calculating the required 
number of public toilets under the Health Act;
